A physical location, for example using text to provide an address, Geo-coordinates, etc.

specification.body: Classifier metaproperty value must be stereotyped «Location» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: String describing the address of the ActualLocation, i.e. "1600 Pennsylvania avenue", "The White House"
Enumerated value describing the kind of ActualLocation.
String describing a location kind that is not in the LocationKind enumerated list
Boolean that indicates if the ActualLocation address is embedded in the ActualLocation name. By default = false.
A definition of the environmental factors in which something exists or functions. The definition of an Environment element can be further defined using EnvironmentKind.
Captures the kind of Environment.
An abstract grouping of elements that can be affected by Risk.

A type that represents a situation involving exposure to danger of AffectableElements (e.g. Assets, Processes, Capabilities, Opportunities, or Enterprise Goals) where the effects of such exposure can be characterized in terms of the likelihood of occurrence of a given threat and the potential adverse consequences of that threat's occurrence.
An abstraction relating a Risk to an organizational role that is responsible for executing the risk mitigation in the specific context or configuration.

specification.body: Value for the client metaproperty must be stereotyped «ResourceRole» or its specializations.
Value for the supplier metaproperty must be stereotyped «Risk» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: An abstraction relating a Risk to an organizational resource that is responsible for executing the risk mitigation.

specification.body: Value for the client metaproperty must be stereotyped «OrganizationalResource» or its specializations.
Value for the supplier metaproperty must be stereotyped «Risk» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: A dependency relating a Security Control to a Risk. Mitigation is established to manage risk and could be represented as an overall strategy or through techniques (mitigation configurations) and procedures (SecurityProcesses).

specification.body: Value for the client metaproperty must be stereotyped «SecurityControl» or its specializations.
Value for the supplier metaproperty must be stereotyped «Risk» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: A dependency that asserts that a Risk is applicable to an Asset.

specification.body: Value for the client metaproperty must be stereotyped «Risk» or its specializations.
Value for the supplier metaproperty must be stereotyped «AffectableElement» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: A dependency that asserts that a Risk is applicable to an AssetRole in the specific context or configuration.

specification.body: Value for the client metaproperty must be stereotyped «Risk» or its specializations.
Value for the supplier metaproperty must be stereotyped «AssetRole» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: An instance of a Risk. A value holder for Risk Measurements.

specification.body: Value for the classifier metaproperty must be stereotyped by «Risk» or its specializations.

ownedComment.body: Enables association of an ActualRisk to an actual organizational role that is responsible for executing the actual mitigation.
Asserts that an ActualRisk is applicable to an ActualResource.
